<br>
There's really not much to persuade me out of thinking that there should be more crush  armsfolk though.  I'm probably just arrogant, but again I'll post, a seemingly very nice chain keys off Maul(Taunt), and Maul should be spammed quite a bit if one is the main tank.<br>
<br>
Oh, I think Mythic had the idea of the light tank maybe in the last 6 months of developing.  They'd already thought up the infiltrator, nightsahde and shadowblade so they just copied everything from the CDW line and pasted it onto the merc, including the style anim.  While the styles looked perfectly fine with the straight bladed swords, if not a bit politically incorrect, they didn't expect any mercs to actually spec crush, even though they made a few left-hander crushers.<br>
<br>
What they could do to fix that would be to use a specific set of anims depending on which kind of weapons are in the two hands.  If they used two different kind of weaps in each hand they could just use the anim of the weapon type that the CDW style was firing off of(I.E.  You just used the style off of your left hand, which has a slasher, you do a slash anim. You use the style off your right, which has a thruster, you do the thrust anim).<br>
<br>
Maybe on the slasher spec they could do the following:<br>
Starts off with a quick but very brutal uppercut style anim, but is quickly followed by a horizontal, but quick again, swipe from the left hand, mainly so the hand axe would like fine in the left hand again.<br>
<br>
They could leave thrusters the same since DW anims were pretty much built for thrust infis.<br>
<br>
